This paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are core topics in game theory and economics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses the use of prior distributions, which suggests a connection to Bayesian methods and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with revenue maximization, which is a central topic in cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The technical methods used in the paper involve upper-bounding and payment identity, which are related to algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with risk-averse preferences, which is a topic in decision theory and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category.
